-- Disney's ABC Took All the Risk for `Millionaire,' Lawyer Says at Trial
-- Edvard Pettersson
-- 2010-06-30T00:19:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/disney-s-abc-took-all-the-risk-for-millionaire-lawyer-says-at-trial.html

          
          
             Walt Disney Co.’s ABC network took
100 percent of the risk for putting “Who Wants to Be a
Millionaire” on U.S. television and the quiz show’s U.K.
creator knew the network run wouldn’t make money, a lawyer for
Disney said at the end of a jury trial over profits from the
show.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Edvard Pettersson in Los Angeles at 
 epettersson@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        